    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-16T06:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-16T06:35:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1875: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-16T15:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 16, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>161. Reference to my No. 157, May 15, 2 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m. Minister
                    of War informs me Soviet authorities have now given permission for total of 1500
                    Iranian troops to proceed Rezaieh area. He stated that in his opinion 5,000
                    troops are necessary to restore and maintain order in Rezaieh and Tabriz and he
                    is consequently requesting Soviet authorities to agree to the sending of
                    additional troops.</p>
                <p>Copy to Tabriz.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
